0010|#PLOT <data> / TYPE=FACES
S   |      <    >
0011|*plots multidimensional data as Chernoff's faces.
0012|*Reference: Chernoff,H.(1973) Using faces to represent points in
0013|*           k-dimensional space graphically, JASA,68,361-368.
0015|*The mapping from data to various features of the face is defined by a
0016|*VARIABLES list written after the PLOT line.
0017|*To create this list, it is best to activate PLOT (with TYPE=FACES)
0018|*without any list. Then a model of the list with appropriate comments
0019|*will be displayed below the current PLOT line.
0020|*A typical list is following:
0022|*PLOT <data> / TYPE=FACES
S   |      <    >
0023|*VARIABLES: xmin      xmax     Features                       fmin fmax
0024|*<X1>      <min X1>  <max X1>  Radius_to_corner_of_face_OP    0.6  1.0
S   | <  >      <      >  <      >
0025|*<X2>      <min X2>  <max X2>  Angle_of_OP_to_horizontal      0.0  0.6
S   | <  >      <      >  <      >
0026|*<X3>      <min X3>  <max X3>  Vertical_size_of_face_OU       0.6  1.0
S   | <  >      <      >  <      >
0027|*<X4>      <min X4>  <max X4>  Eccentricity_of_upper_face     0.5  1.5
S   | <  >      <      >  <      >
0028|*<X5>      <min X5>  <max X5>  Eccentricity_of_lower_face     0.5  1.5
S   | <  >      <      >  <      >
0029|*<X6>      <min X6>  <max X6>  Length_of_nose                 0.1  0.5
S   | <  >      <      >  <      >
0030|*<X7>      <min X7>  <max X7>  Vertical_position_of_mouth     0.2  0.8
S   | <  >      <      >  <      >
0031|*<X8>      <min X8>  <max X8>  Curvature_of_mouth_1/R        -4.0  4.0
S   | <  >      <      >  <      >
0032|*<X9>      <min X9>  <max X9>  Width_of_mouth                 0.2  1.0
S   | <  >      <      >  <      >
0033|*<X10>     <min X10> <max X10> Vertical_position_of_eyes      0.0  0.4
S   | <   >     <       > <       >
0034|*<X11>     <min X11> <max X11> Separation_of_eyes             0.3  0.8
S   | <   >     <       > <       >
0035|*<X12>     <min X12> <max X12> Slant_of_eyes                 -0.5  0.5
S   | <   >     <       > <       >
0036|*<X13>     <min X13> <max X13> Eccentricity_of_eyes           0.3  1.0
S   | <   >     <       > <       >
0037|*<X14>     <min X14> <max X14> Size_of_eyes                   0.1  0.2
S   | <   >     <       > <       >
0038|*<X15>     <min X15> <max X15> Position_of_pupils            -0.1  0.1
S   | <   >     <       > <       >
0039|*<X16>     <min X16> <max X16> Vertical_position_of_eyebrows  0.2  0.4
S   | <   >     <       > <       >
0040|*<X17>     <min X17> <max X17> Slant_of_eyebrows             -0.5  0.5
S   | <   >     <       > <       >
0041|*<X18>     <min X18> <max X18> Size_of_eyebrows               0.1  0.5
S   | <   >     <       > <       >
0042|*END of plotting specifications
0044|*The variables selected will be mapped to various features linearly so
0045|*that xmin -> fmin and xmax -> fmax. This scheme may be freely edited
S   |            >                >
0046|*by altering xmin and ymin values (eventually also fmin and fmax) to
0047|*achieve a desired result. For example, the influence of certain variable
0048|*could be reversed by changing its xmin and xmax values.
0049|*To keep certain features constant, use character '-' instead of a
0050|*variable. Then (fmin+fmax)/2 will be used as the value of the feature
0051|*for all observations.
0052|*The default list obtained after activating PLOT  with TYPE=FACES without
0053|*a list has '-' as each variable, '*' for xmin and '**' for xmax.
0054|*If now '-' is replaced by a name of a variable and PLOT is activated,
0055|*the faces are plotted by using the true minimum value value in place of
0056|*'*' and maximum value in place of '**'. (The list is automatically
0057|*updated with true values ending to '*' or '**'.)
0058|*The user may then add various features gradually and see their effects
0059|*immediately. The mapping can be fixed by erasing '*'s.
0061|*The PLOT operation for Chernoff's faces may be supported by the
0062|*extra specifications HEADER,HOME,SIZE,XDIV,YDIV as in any curve plotting
0063|*schemes.
0064|*Furthermore two special specifications LABEL and FSIZE are available.
0065|*LABEL=<label variable> selects the name of the observation to be
S   |       <              >
0066|*printed under the face. If LABEL is omitted, # of observation will be
0067|*used as default.
0068|*FSIZE=c gives the side length of the square to be used as an area for
0069|*each face. c is given in plotting units and has the default value
0070|*which is one fifth of the current width of the plot.
0071|*The specifications SIZE,XDIV,YDIV and FSIZE determine together the
0072|*layout for the faces.
0074|*On the screen (GPLOT), the various parts of the faces can be drawn with
0075|*different colors possibly depending on values of selected variables.
0076|*The face and the eyes can also be painted.
0077|*The colors are selected by adding a COLORS list (before the END line
0078|*in the VARIABLES list).
0079|*A model of such a list is obtained by activating GPLOT with TYPE=FACES
0080|*without a VARIABLES list.
