0099|#PLOT <data> / TYPE=STARS
S   |      <    >
0100|*plots multidimensional data as star symbol plots.
0101|*Reference: Chambers,Cleveland,Kleiner,P.A.Tukey: Graphical Methods for
0102|*           Data Analysis. The Wadsworth Statistics/Probability Series, 1983
0103|*           (pp. 158-161)
0104|*Each observation of m active variables is represented as a set of rays
0105|*whose directions are equally spaced around the circle and the length
0106|*of the ray corresponding to the variable x is
0107|*     (1-c)*(x-xmin)/(xmax-xmin)+c .
0108|*c is a constant with the default value 0.2. Another value for c can be
0109|*selected by entering the TYPE specification in the form TYPE=STARS,c .
0110|*The order of activate variables in the stars is determined by the alpha-
0111|*betic order of their mask symbols and secondarily by their order in the
0112|*data set.
0113|*The general layout of the star symbol plots in the plotting region is
0114|*the same as that of Chernoff's faces. The LABEL and FSIZE specifications
0115|- shadow %: [LINK(q1e_01.html)] [/LINK]
0116|*are available as well (See FACES?).
S   |                            %%%%%
0118|- shadow a: [LINK(q1d_01.html)]
0119|*  M = more information on multivariate plotting
S   |   a                                           |
