0126|#PLOT <data> / TYPE=PROFILES
S   |      <    >
0127|*plots multidimensional data as profile symbol plots.
0128|*Reference: Chambers,Cleveland,Kleiner,P.A.Tukey: Graphical Methods for
0129|*           Data Analysis. The Wadsworth Statistics/Probability Series, 1983
0130|*           (pp. 159-163)
0131|*Each observation of m active variables is represented as a broken line
0132|*connecting points (1,y1),(2,y2),...,(m,ym) where y coordinates are
0133|*the scaled values y=x/max(abs(x)).
0134|*Also the base line and the vertical side lines are plottted for each
0135|*profile.
0136|*The order of activate variables in the profiles is determined by the alpha-
0137|*betic order of their mask symbols and secondarily by their order in the
0138|*data set.
0139|*The general layout of the profile symbol plots in the plotting region is
0140|*the same as that of Chernoff's faces. The LABEL and FSIZE specifications
0141|- shadow %: [LINK(q1e_01.html)] [/LINK]
0142|*are available as well (See FACES?).
